  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Anticipating Future Developments**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the AI Spam Shield application\'s future. I\'ve designed a mockup of a phone frame, a dashboard showcasing a \"100% Secured\" animation, stats, critical threats, and call and SMS log views. I\'m exploring enhancements now.\n\n\n**Developing UI Mockup Iterations**\n\nI\'ve been working on refining the UI. It\'s a client-side mockup in a phone container, given the constraints. It doesn\'t actually intercept calls, but I\'m thinking about how to improve it. My focus is on the next steps: an interactive demo mode, a detailed analysis modal for intercepts, and possibly integrating the Gemini API to analyze typed messages dynamically. I\'m exploring adding these features to strengthen the prototype.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have set up the core UI and navigation for the \"AI Spam Shield\" dashboard in a mobile-first interface. \n\nTo take this application to the next level, here are a few directions we could go:\n\n- **Live Simulation Mode:** We can add a \"Simulate Attack\" button that allows you to type in a mock SMS or upload an audio transcript, which would then be processed by Gemini in real-time to generate a threat score and analysis on the dashboard.\n- **Detailed Intercept Breakdown:** We can build a detailed view for when you click on a specific log entry. This could display a simulated audio waveform, a transcript of the scam, and a detailed breakdown of the AI\'s reasoning for blocking it.\n- **Onboarding Flow:** We can build a first-time setup sequence that simulates the process of granting Android permissions (Phone, SMS, Contacts) and initializing the Core Protection engine.\n- **Custom Rule Engine:** We can expand the Settings view to allow you to configure custom blocking rules (e.g., \"Block all numbers from this area code\" or \"Flag anything mentioning \'IRS\'\").\n\nWhich of these would you like to focus on next, or do you have another feature in mind?"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 128948909
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
